+++</md></sn><sn><md>## The Sun {.text-center}

+++ later

The Sun is the `central star` of our solar system and the primary `source of light and energy` that sustains life on Earth. It is a `massive sphere of hot plasma` held together by gravity and powered by nuclear fusion reactions at its core.

---

### Formation of the Sun

:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-lg-7
The Sun formed about `4.6 billion years ago` from a ++giant molecular cloud++ composed mostly of `hydrogen and helium`. Under the influence of *gravity*:

1. The cloud began to `collapse and spin`, forming a **protostar**.
2. As the material compressed, temperature and pressure increased in the core.
3. When the core reached around **10 million ¬∞C**, ++nuclear fusion of hydrogen into helium began++.
4. This marked the birth of the Sun as a main-sequence star.
